- **Type**:
- Optical Encoders: Using light to detect position changes, optical encoders offer high precision and accuracy.
- Magnetic Encoders: Employing magnetic fields for position sensing, magnetic encoders are durable and reliable.
- Mechanical Encoders: Utilizing physical movement for position detection, mechanical encoders are robust and cost-effective.
- Capacitive Encoders: Capacitive encoders measure changes in capacitance for position tracking, offering high resolution.

- **Application**:
- Material Handling: Rotary encoders facilitate precise positioning in material handling equipment for efficient operations.
- Machine Tools: In the machine tool industry, rotary encoders enable accurate control of machining processes.
- Motion Systems: Rotary encoders play a crucial role in motion control systems for controlling speed and position.
- Robotics: Robotics applications rely on rotary encoders for precise motion control and navigation.
